Subject: [PATCH 25/25] UI rebuild stage 4: per-tab body density
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Reusable components/Section.jsx — a collapsible content block (default-open
so adoption is non-breaking; title stays visible while collapsed so a safety
headline never hides). Unit-tested (4 cases).

BcmConfigTab: open as a collapsed INDEX — only the first of the ten themed
categories expands on load; a live search force-opens every matching section.
Turns a ten-hero-banner scroll into a one-screen index.

ProxiTab: adopt Section for the 'two panels — different write semantics'
reference banner; the safety headline stays in the collapsed header, the
detail folds away.

Full suite: 5843 passed (+5 new), broke nothing — the 7 pre-existing
failures (verified on a clean tree) are unchanged.
